"Enmore, Somerset, England","Enmore, Somerset, Eng.":"Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Bridgwater, Somerset, England":"Bridgwater, Somerset, England","Enmore, Eng.":"Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Malet","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: nickname from a diminutive of   Mal   ‘bad’ or from a derivative of the related Old French word <i>maleit</i> ‘accursed’ (see   Mallet   1). Compare   Malette  .","French: from the Old French personal name <i>Malet</i>, a pet form of   Malo   (compare   Mallet   2).","French: variant of   Mallet   3."],"variants":[{"name":"Mal","meanings":["Slovenian: nickname for a physically small man, from <i>mal</i> ‘small, little’.","French (mainly Nord): nickname from <i>mal</i> ‘bad’ (from Latin <i>malus</i>).","Indian (northern states): variant of   Mall  ."]},{"name":"Malette","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gaston, Alphonse, Francois, Jacques, Rejean, Serge.","French: variant or feminine form of   Malet   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this, reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"Baldwin","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>bald</i> ‘bold, brave’ + <i>wine</i> ‘friend’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. In the Middle Ages it was a comparatively common name, which gave rise to a surname. It was borne by the Norman crusader  Baldwin  of Boulogne, who in  1100  was elected first king of Jerusalem, and by four further crusader kings of Jerusalem. It continued to be used by some families in England into the 17th century, but in modern times it normally represents a transferred use of the surname rather than a direct revival of the Norman given name."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":14,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Baldwin Malet II was born about 1245, in Enmore, Somerset, England, his father, William Malet, was 41 and his mother, Mrs. Maria Mallet, was 36. He married Mabel de Deardon about 1264, in England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1279, in his hometown, at the age of 35."},"et":{"about 1245–1279":"umbes 1245–1279","1232–Male":"1232–Surnud","1236–Female":"1236–Surnud","1245–1279":"1245–1279","1247–1287":"1247–1287","1264–Male":"1264–Surnud","1265–1287":"1265–1287","1290–1328":"1290–1328","1206–1264":"1206–1264","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1264":"1264","1290":"1290","1206":"1206","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1236":"1236","1279":"1279","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1232":"1232","living 1272":"1272","about 1245":"umbes 1245","after 1264":"pärast 1264","livg. abt. 1272":"umbes 1272","about 1264":"umbes 1264","1328":"1328","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England","Enmore, Somerset, Eng.":"Enmore, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bridgwater, Somerset, England":"Bridgwater, Somerset, England","Enmore, Eng.":"Enmore, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1245–1279":"noin 1245–1279","1232–Male":"1232–Kuollut","1236–Female":"1236–Kuollut","1245–1279":"1245–1279","1247–1287":"1247–1287","1264–Male":"1264–Kuollut","1265–1287":"1265–1287","1290–1328":"1290–1328","1206–1264":"1206–1264","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1264":"1264","1290":"1290","1206":"1206","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1236":"1236","1279":"1279","1245":"1245